DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _s_p_l_i_t_._s_h  is a Bourne shell (_s_h) script that clears the entire graphics
       screen and divides it into two display frames.   Map  layers  are  then
       displayed  in  each of the two frames.  This command is very useful for
       visually comparing maps (raster, vector, and 3-d views) and can be used
       by  other  GRASS  shell  macros.  It is also useful for creating demos.
       Program parameters are given below.

