              The graphics screen can be split either horizontally  or  verti-
              cally.   The default view splits the screen into two frames, one
              on the left and one on the right (a vertical split).  Some  maps
              (3-d  views)  are better represented with more width then height
              (horizontal split).  The first map name listed  on  the  command
              line  will  be displayed in the top or left window (depending on
              whether the screen was split horizontally  or  vertically),  and
              The  second map will be displayed in the bottom or right window.

